Work In Progress UPDATE! 
The cabin garage is coming to life //

I bought this cabin from its original owner and builder (1986). The bones are strong and the location gives us the opportunity to be in the great outdoors. I wanted to give my family a place where we can escape, create memories, and have a whole lot of fun⚡️

First things first, both the garage and the main cabin needed a siding update. We wanted black, high quality, and a product that represents us. #LoveWhereYouLive @qualityedge 

The roof was just as important. The cabin is surrounded by trees and we get all weather conditions. And I know my wife does not want to use pots and pans as rain collectors. #DrivenByFamily @edcoproducts 

We are excited to add another #lifetime to our cabin so we can pass it down to Jack one day. It means a lot to me to be doing the work myself, with help from my friends, and I can’t wait to show you all the end of this special project. A true #LaborOfLove

A huge shoutout to @84lumber for always having what I want and 
need to make my #Designs come to life. We always get kick out of how the drivers find our location and get our materials up these dirt roads.👏👊

WORK IN PROGRESS // PAINT WHITE

I completely transformed “The Carnival Project” space into a work of #art by designing with @romabiopaints Classico Limewash products.

I wanted these walls to feel larger than life and give them a more artistic appeal. The Limewash paints recreate a timeless white-wash effect that gives your space a tasteful reminder of ancient times and room for creativity. 

The process is made simple... add water to achieve your desired consistency, and mix it. Use the Masonry brush, the bristles hold double the paint and is great for projects with large surface areas.

Its formulated to be removable // wash it off for a distress look with a breathable finish or add more for a bolder feel.

PLUS its eco-friendly, sustainable, and family approved. its mineral based, made with natural ingredients, and toxic free.
